Tibetan herders are being forced to settle in towns by China, disrupting their traditional way of life.
The government's relocation program aims to combat desertification caused by overgrazing and urban sprawl.
Guizhou Province is particularly affected by stone desertification, threatening farmers' livelihoods.
Sandstorms in Minqin County are worsening due to erosion, with 94% of the area turning into desert.
China is implementing measures to protect arable land and combat soil erosion, benefiting millions of residents.
Efforts to reverse erosion have increased grain production and improved livelihoods, showing progress in soil conservation.
